{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rage-lemur-act","description":"Mirror how validity is produced: extend the kernel `verification` contract with a small\nNOVELTY sub-answer set and feed the verifier (Pass-2 ONLY) the prior findings so it can\nanswer them factually (\"does this finding correspond to a prior finding?\"). Pass-1 stays\nunanchored (no prior findings → full recall, no sycophancy). The verifier scores novelty\nand severity independently and is never told the drop consequence.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `verification` contract carries a novelty sub-answer set (yes|no|insufficient) in `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py`\n- [ ] Pass-2 receives prior findings; Pass-1 does not (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py`, `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_verifier.md`)\n- [ ] Novelty questions are factual (match-prior), not \"should I downrank\"\n- [ ] Verifier eval still passes (validity + impact discrimination unaffected)","id":"e344-68ef-febe-4c37","parent_id":"7d43-49c5-bc4d-4926","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Persist finding text in the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar for re-grounding"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782753968403688001,"uuid":"d5b44001-9bb8-484f-9d48-45bfffa7150d"}